entries.meaning: A periwinkle or its shell, of family Littorinidae.
examples: […]  because the inward Eare is intorted like a winkle-shell, and hangeth as a bell in thee steeple of the body, it easily perceiueth all appulsions of the Ayre.

entries.meaning: Any one of various marine spiral gastropods, especially, in the United States, either of two species Busycotypus canaliculatus and Busycon carica.
(children's slang) The penis, especially that of a boy rather than that of a man.

verbs.description: winkle (third-person singular simple present winkles, present participle winkling, simple past and past participle winkled)

entries.meaning: Synonym of winkle out (“to acquire or extract with difficulty”)
